Anders Koppel (born 17 July 1947 in Copenhagen) is a co-founder in 1967 of the rock group Savage Rose.
From 1976 to 2012 he was a member of the trio Bazaar.
Anders Koppel has twice received the Danish film award Robert for best film score (1994 and 1996).
He began playing the organ in 1966.
